<subSubSection id="C368652E935A8E07F2AAFDD3FCB6FD27" pageId="3" pageNumber="487" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A5935A8E07F2AAFDD3FCB6FD27" blockId="3.[151,1437,577,928]" pageId="3" pageNumber="487">
<materialsCitation id="3B1A3CF8935A8E07F2AAFDD3FCB2FD27" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3798147306" collectorName="B. Jenisson &amp; J. Serrano" country="Morocco" location="Tanger" pageId="3" pageNumber="487" specimenCount="3" typeStatus="holotype">
The specimen hereby recognized as 
<typeStatus id="54C98807935A8E07F00CFDD3FD42FD90" box="[561,659,577,603]" pageId="3" pageNumber="487">holotype</typeStatus>
is a male bearing the labels: “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935A8E07F1D7FDD3FBB3FD90" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1826" box="[1002,1122,577,603]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Ditomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="487" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cephalotes">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935A8E07F1D7FDD3FBB3FD90" box="[1002,1122,577,603]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="487">cephalotes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
m.”, “ 
<collectingCountry id="F3657635935A8E07F696FDD3FB2CFD90" box="[1195,1277,577,603]" name="Morocco" pageId="3" pageNumber="487">Tanger</collectingCountry>
. 
<collectorName id="26875373935A8E07F734FDD0FA5FFD90" box="[1289,1422,577,604]" pageId="3" pageNumber="487">B. Jenisson</collectorName>
”, “ex-Museo Chaudoir” and “ 
<typeStatus id="54C98807935A8E07F3F0FDF7FDE9FDB4" box="[461,568,613,639]" pageId="3" pageNumber="487">Holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935A8E07F066FDF4FC02FDB4" authority="Dejean, 1826" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1826" box="[603,979,613,639]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Ditomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="487" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cephalotes">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935A8E07F066FDF4FCE9FDB4" box="[603,824,613,639]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="487">Ditomus cephalotes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935A8E07F103FDF7FC02FDB4" author="Dejean, P. F. M. A." box="[830,979,613,639]" pageId="3" pageNumber="487" refId="ref10638" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. (1826) Species general des coleopteres, de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Tome second. Crevot, Paris, viii + 501 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 8863" type="book" year="1826">Dejean, 1826</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
desig. by 
<collectorName id="26875373935A8E07F67EFDF4FB69FDB4" box="[1091,1208,613,640]" pageId="3" pageNumber="487">J. Serrano</collectorName>
”. Thus, labels match the description: 
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935A8E07F371FD1BFE71FD0C" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="487">
Il se trouve sur la côte de Barbarie, et il m’a été donné par M. le comte de Jenisson comme venant des environs de 
<collectingCountry id="F3657635935A8E07F36FFD3CFE71FD0C" box="[338,416,686,711]" name="Morocco" pageId="3" pageNumber="487">Tanger</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
. Since this was the sole specimen found in Dejean’s collection at Paris with the original labels, the specimen is recognized as the 
<typeStatus id="54C98807935A8E07F059FD43FD17FD20" box="[612,710,721,747]" pageId="3" pageNumber="487">holotype</typeStatus>
by monotypy
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C368652E935A8E07F2FAFD67FD06FCB7" pageId="3" pageNumber="487" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A5935A8E07F2FAFD67FD06FCB7" blockId="3.[151,1437,577,928]" pageId="3" pageNumber="487">
The species may be easily identified following the keys of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935A8E07F15EFD64FBD0FCC4" author="Fuente de la, J. M." box="[867,1025,757,784]" pageId="3" pageNumber="487" refId="ref10490" refString="Fuente de la, J. M. (1927) Tablas analiticas para la clasificacion de los coleopteros de la Peninsula Iberica. Adephaga: I Cicindelidae, II Carabidae. J. Bosch, Barcelona, 415 pp." type="book" year="1927">Fuente (1927)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935A8E07F605FD67FB36FCDB" author="Antoine, M." box="[1080,1255,757,784]" pageId="3" pageNumber="487" pagination="315 - 465" refId="ref10238" refString="Antoine, M. (1959) Coleopteres Carabiques du Maroc. Troisieme partie. Memoires de la Societe des Sciences Naturelles et Physiques du Maroc, Nouvelle Serie, Zoologie, 6, 315 - 465." type="journal article" year="1959">Antoine (1959)</bibRefCitation>
. The taxonomic placement and limits of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935A8E07F01CFC8BFD62FCF8" authorityName="Solier" authorityYear="1835" box="[545,691,793,819]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Odontocarus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="487" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935A8E07F01CFC8BFD62FCF8" box="[545,691,793,819]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="487">Odontocarus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been subjected to many controversies (see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935A8E07F6EFFC88FAB5FCF8" author="Wrase, D. W." box="[1234,1380,793,820]" pageId="3" pageNumber="487" pagination="931 - 964" refId="ref12478" refString="Wrase, D. W. (1994) Revision der Carterus angustus-Gruppe und Bemerkungen zur Gattung Carterus Dejean (Col., Carabidae, Harpalini). Linzer Biologische Beitrage, 26, 931 - 964." type="journal article" year="1994">Wrase, 1994</bibRefCitation>
), but nowadays is currently ranked as an independent genus; it includes seven species with a 
<collectingRegion id="49B6F847935A8E07F646FCAFFB16FC9C" box="[1147,1223,829,855]" country="France" name="Centre" pageId="3" pageNumber="487">Centro</collectingRegion>
Asiatic Mediterranean distribution pattern (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935A8E07F38AFCF3FD1AFCB7" author="Kataev, B. M. &amp; Wrase, D. W." box="[439,715,865,892]" pageId="3" pageNumber="487" pagination="1810" refId="ref11655" refString="Kataev, B. M. &amp; Wrase, D. W. (2017 b) Subtribe Ditomina Bonelli, 1810. In: Lobl, I. &amp; Lobl, D. (Eds.), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Vol. 1. Revised and Updated Edition. Brill, Leiden, pp. 509 - 514." type="book chapter" year="2017">Kataev &amp; Wrase, 2017b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C368652E935A8E07F2FAFC17FA5CFC54" box="[199,1421,901,928]" pageId="3" pageNumber="487" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A5935A8E07F2FAFC17FA5CFC54" blockId="3.[151,1437,577,928]" box="[199,1421,901,928]" pageId="3" pageNumber="487">
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935A8E07F2FAFC17FD56FC6B" authority="(Dejean, 1826)" baseAuthorityName="Dejean" baseAuthorityYear="1826" box="[199,647,901,928]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Odontocarus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="487" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cephalotes">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935A8E07F2FAFC17FE09FC54" box="[199,472,901,927]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="487">Odontocarus cephalotes</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935A8E07F3DAFC17FDAEFC6B" author="Dejean, P. F. M. A." box="[487,639,901,928]" pageId="3" pageNumber="487" refId="ref10638" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. (1826) Species general des coleopteres, de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Tome second. Crevot, Paris, viii + 501 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 8863" type="book" year="1826">Dejean, 1826</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
is the single species of the genus inhabiting the West Mediterranean.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
